  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "MANAGER",
  "description": "<p><strong>1. Experience & Skills</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Proven management experience</strong> (usually 2–5+ years) in a barber shop, salon or related service environment.</p></li><li><p>Strong leadership, people-management and organisational skills.</p></li><li><p>Good <strong>customer service and communication skills</strong> — able to deal with clients and staff effectively.</p></li><li><p>Ability to <strong>problem-solve and handle complaints</strong> with professionalism. </p></li></ul><p><strong>2. Barbering Knowledge (Often an Advantage)</strong></p><ul><li><p>Familiarity with barber skills, styling techniques, and product knowledge can be beneficial, though some managers focus primarily on operations rather than cutting.</p></li><li><p>Some roles may require the ability to perform barber duties when needed. </p></li></ul><p><strong>3. Tech & Admin</strong></p><ul><li><p>Proficiency with business tools (POS systems, scheduling tools, basic office software such as Microsoft Office).</p></li><li><p>Strong organizational and multitasking ability. </p></li></ul><p><strong>4. Personal Attributes</strong></p><ul><li><p>Customer-centric, proactive, upbeat and professional in grooming and attitude.</p></li><li><p>Strong work ethic, able to work in a fast-paced environment.</p></li><li><p>Excellent team player with leadership qualities. </p></li></ul><p><strong>5. Education & Certification</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Diploma or degree in business, hospitality, management or related field</strong> may be preferred but not always mandatory.</p></li><li><p>Barber certification/license and industry training is a plus (especially if hands-on barber skills are part of the duties). </p></li></ul>",
